#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:151
msgid ""
"Objects can be linked in order to create shared movements (movements that"
" all the linked objects share with the parent object) and relative "
"movements (movements that are the sum of the object's own movement and "
"the movement of its parent object)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:153
msgid ""
"As parent objects can be linked, in their turn, to other moving objects, "
"it is possible to define a complex hierarchy of transformations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:155
msgid ""
"The hierarchy between objects can be edited by setting links that allow "
"you to set parent and linked objects: columns/layers can be linked to "
"other columns/layers, pegbars, the table or cameras; pegbars can be "
"linked to other pegbars, the table or cameras; cameras can be linked to "
"any object in order to create complex shots, for example with a camera "
"following the movement of a character in the scene."
