msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:371
msgid ""
"When selected, the Tracker tool (|tracker|) allows you to define one or "
"several regions in an image, by defining a center and a size; regions can"
" also be connected to one another to better track points having a visual "
"geometrical relationship. The region defined with the tool sets both, the"
" *pattern* that the tracking system will try to recognize in the "
"following images, and the *size* of the search area where it will look "
"for it (that will be of approximately twice that region)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:373
msgid ""
"Once areas to be tracked are defined in the first frame of a range, it's "
"possible to automatically track the regions in a selected range, by "
"specifying the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:375
msgid "|tracking_options|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:377
msgid ""
"**Threshold** sets the amount of difference between the defined pattern "
"and the recognized one. When using low values, the tracking system will "
"look for an area with an almost identical pattern, and when using high "
"values, will look for an area that can be quite different from the "
"original one. This means that if the value is too low, it’s more likely "
"for the tracking to fail on certain images; if too high, the tracking may"
" fail by following the wrong areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:379
msgid ""
"**Sensitivity** sets how often the defined pattern has to be updated "
"according to the variation it may have in the following images. For the "
"maximum value, the pattern will be updated after each image is tracked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:381
msgid ""
"**Variable Region Size**, when activated, will look for the defined "
"pattern considering also the different sizes that it can have in the "
"following images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:383
msgid ""
"**Include Background**, when activated, it considers the background as "
"part of the defined pattern. It can be deactivated when tracking an "
"element whose background does not affect the pattern, such as a "
"green/blue screen background."
msgstr ""

